Overall Business Insights:
1)Campaign duration is typically around 18 days, with most campaigns lasting between 11 and 24 days.
2)Campaign reach is substantial, averaging around 55,000 impressions, though there is significant variation.
3)Profit-loss classes are well balanced (roughly 50% profitable and 50% not), making the dataset suitable for classification tasks.
4)The average conversion rate is 22.49%, indicating that about one in five users who click an ad complete the desired action.
5)The maximum conversion rate of 338.43% is unusual and should be investigated before drawing business conclusions from it, especially if the data is expected to reflect real-world marketing campaigns.